==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fulmine
<hw>Ful"mine</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To shoot; to dart like
lightning; to fulminate; to utter with authority or vehemence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She <qex>fulmined</qex> out her scorn of laws Salique.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fulmineous</ent>⟦br⟧
